    "abstractNote": "There is a little-known tradition which attests to Paul\u2019s decapitated head being lost just outside Rome and discovered much later by a shepherd. I will present four Syriac versions of this tradition, including the Letter of (Pseudo-)Dionysius the Areopagite to Timothy, a thirteenth century encyclopaedia by an East Syrian bishop called The Book of the Bee, and two hagiographic manuscripts. All of these attest to Paul\u2019s head miraculously re-attaching to his body during a vigil/experiment in Rome. I will examine and compare these texts to see what motifs and possible historical events lie behind this unusual posthumous miracle.",
